properties.Name: ReserveType
properties.Description:
A classification or categorization of reserve types.

Ex:
- Statutory Reserve - the amount required to be set aside by government regulators to ensure that a company remains solvent
- IBNR (Incurred but not reported) - reflect claims that have taken place but have not been reported by the insurer. In some cases this will cover claims that take haven't been noticed or reported, like major storm damage.
- Claim Reserve - amount set aside to cover the amount expected to be paid to the insured along with expenses to the insurer such as legal fees.

Columns.Name: ReserveTypeId
Columns.Description: The unique identifier of a Reserve Type.

Columns.Description: The name of a Reserve Type.

Columns.Description: The description of a Reserve Type.
